Understanding the Data Ecosystem
  A data ecosystem consists of various elements that interact to produce, manage, store, organize, analyze, and share data, including hardware, software, and the people who use them.
  The cloud serves as a virtual location for storing data online, allowing data access over the internet rather than on local hard drives.

Common Misconceptions in Data Analytics
  Data scientists and data analysts have different roles: data scientists create new questions using data, while analysts find answers to existing questions.
  Data analysis involves collecting and organizing data to draw conclusions, whereas data analytics is a broader concept encompassing all aspects of managing and using data.
